

  The Shadow of the Third Moon (demo) - Configuration guide



Configuration:


Briefing screen mode: select a 640x480 screen mode (256 colors)

1-screen mode: select a 320x240 (chunky) screen mode

2-screen mode: select a 320x240 screen mode (AGA chipset)

Save path: locates the save path (default: PROGDIR:Save/)

Objects path: select objects set for 4 or 8MB Fast RAM:

              1-  PROGDIR:Objects-VectBit/4MB-FAST
              2-  PROGDIR:Objects-VectBit/8MB-FAST

Graphics path: select language set:

              1-  PROGDIR:Graf-set/English
              2-  PROGDIR:Graf-set/Italiano
              3-  PROGDIR:Graf-set/Deutsch

Maps path: locates the maps path (default: PROGDIR:Maps/)

Sounds path: locates the sound path (default: PROGDIR:Sound/)

C2P routine: (default: PROGDIR:C2P/)

              1- 68030        (C2P_68030)
              2- 68030        (C2P_Chunky4)
              3- 68040        (C2P_68040_FRam4)
              4- 68040-68060  (C2P_NaOC2P)

Graphic mode: AGA 2 screens (AGA-C2P)
              Cybergraphix (only v2.x)
              Generic RTG (O.S. RTG , all chunky cabable GFXboards

Trasparent smoke: on-off

Fast Load: only AGA chipset (speedup with 640x480 gfx)

CDROM device: locates the ATA/SCSI device

CDROM unit: select unit (ATA/SCSI)

Save: save preferences


N.B: scsi.device users must insert "scsi.device" manually "scsi.device"
     at CDROM device field. This demo don't work without a CDROM control
     device.


**********************************************************************



Ingame preferences (please press "Esc" ingame):


Detailed near: on-off

Detailed far: on-off
range: 1 up to 150 (1 max, 150 min)

Panorama (field of vision)
range: 1 up to 32 (1 min, 32 max)

Initial joy. (digital only) speed:
range: 1 up to 40 (1 min, 40 max)

Joy. acceleration:
range: 0 up to 30 (0 min, 30 max)

Sky: on-off

Smoke: on-off

VectBit system: on-off

FPS counter: on-off


Ingame keys:

F2: missile view
F10: end mission
A: engine up
Z: engine down
1: engine up (vertical engine)
Q: engine down (vertical engine)
S: select weapon system
X: multiple fire
D: wingman attack (if available, against selected target)
E: next target
R: prev. target
Esc: ingame preferences

mouse: direction
 LMB: fire
 RMB: select target

Joystick (digital, if selected): direction
 Fire 1: fire
 Fire 2: select target

Numeric key pad:

/: internal cockpit view
*: external view
+: zoom in
-: zoom out
1 up to 9: change view


